This derivative modifies the original. Notable changes:
  - Default flow reduced to a 3-step interview / draft / review; the eval,
    description-tuning, and blind-comparison machinery is gated behind an
    opt-in capability checkpoint rather than run by default.
  - Added an "ultra-<single-token>-<verber>" skill naming convention.
  - Review step presents structural decisions as bullets instead of pasting
    the full SKILL.md into the conversation.
  - Skill descriptions kept trigger-only; specification moved into the body.
  - References reorganized into writing-guide / evals / description-tuning /
    blind-comparison / environments for progressive disclosure.
  - Claude Code treated as the primary environment; Claude.ai / Cowork
    instructions moved into a reference file.
  - Added a provenance gate at skill creation: original skills receive an
    MIT LICENSE automatically; derived skills receive the upstream LICENSE
    plus a NOTICE stating attribution and changes.
  - Added a repository publishing workflow (default into the skills repo,
    branch, create or modify, link, verify, gated commit) that delegates
    branch and commit authoring to sibling skills; opening the PR is left
    to the user.
  - Added a per-skill README standard (Traditional Chinese, fixed sections,
    objective tone, full-width heading spacers, two-level bullets) captured
    in references/readme-guide.md.

The bundled eval tooling under scripts/, agents/, eval-viewer/, and
assets/eval_review.html is carried substantially unmodified from the
original skill-creator. The file assets/license-mit.txt is original to
this derivative.
